<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="153" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1127,219,1556]" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,393,1307,1331]" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": LEVASSEUR" authorityYear="1966" box="[398,687,1309,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Mentophilonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triseriatus">
<emphasis box="[398,687,1309,1332]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">Mentophilonthus triseriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hromádka, 2009" authorityName="Hromádka" authorityYear="2009" box="[867,981,1309,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Mentophilonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="struthio" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[867,981,1309,1332]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">M. struthio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[986,1067,1308,1331]" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from which it may be distinguished by the shorter antennae, coarse punctation of the scutellum and darker body colouration. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": LEVASSEUR" authorityYear="1966" box="[414,708,1373,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Mentophilonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triseriatus">
<emphasis box="[414,708,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">Mentophilonthus triseriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Hromádka, 2009" authorityName="Hromádka" authorityYear="2009" box="[996,1091,1373,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Menthophilonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[996,1091,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">M. equus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="34" pageNumber="153" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by longer eyes, wider head and sparser punctation of the scutellum, and it differs from both 
<taxonomicName authority="Hromádka, 2009" authorityName="Hromádka" authorityYear="2009" box="[205,324,1437,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Mentophilonthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="struthio" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[205,324,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">M. struthio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[330,413,1436,1459]" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hromádka, 2009" authorityName="Hromádka" authorityYear="2009" box="[464,562,1437,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Menthophilonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[464,562,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">M. equus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,651,1436,1459]" pageId="34" pageNumber="153" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1127,219,1556]" box="[151,396,1467,1491]" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1467,1491]" pageId="34" pageNumber="153">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
